    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Are School Vouchers the Answer?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Glenn Woiceshyn says school vouchers will improce education system for everyone, not just blacks (William Safire Aug 31 Op-Ed)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Vouchers Help Blacks'' by William Safire (column, Aug. 31):</p>
        <p>School vouchers will improve the education system for everyone. Vouchers give consumers freedom to purchase the best education available, thereby creating an economic incentive for better schools.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Vouchers Help Blacks'' by William Safire (column, Aug. 31):</p>
        <p>School vouchers will improve the education system for everyone. Vouchers give consumers freedom to purchase the best education available, thereby creating an economic incentive for better schools.</p>
        <p>It should be obvious why Al Gore strongly opposes vouchers: individual rights would be enhanced at the expense of government coercion.</p>
        <p>GLENN WOICESHYN  Calgary, Alberta, Aug. 31, 2000</p>
      </block>
